      "en": {"name": "Mrs. Patricia Miller, 52", "bio": "Retired teacher · Has savings\nSkeptical of salespeople\nSays: \"I don't need insurance. I have savings.\"", "greeting": "Hello. I understand you'd like to talk about insurance. I have to say up front — I already have savings, so I'm not sure I need this.", "tasks": "① Build trust with a skeptical client\n② Uncover her real concerns\n③ Schedule a follow-up meeting", "openers": ["Mrs. Miller, I understand you have savings. May I ask — if something unexpected happened, how long would those savings support your family?", "Mrs. Miller, I am not here to pressure you. I have one question — what would your family do financially if you were no longer here?", "Mrs. Miller, many of my clients had the same view before we spoke. May I share what changed their thinking?"]},
      "zh": {"name": "吳女士，52歲", "bio": "退休教師 · 有積蓄\n對推銷人員保持警惕\n她說：「我不需要保險，我有積蓄。」", "greeting": "你好，聽說你想跟我談保險。我先說清楚，我自己有積蓄，應該不太需要這個。", "tasks": "① 與難搞的客戶建立信任\n② 發現她真正的擔憂\n③ 安排下次會面", "openers": ["吳女士，我了解您在財務上做得很好。我想請教您——如果發生意外，您的積蓄能保護您的家人多久？", "吳女士，我今天不是來賣保險的。我只有一個問題——如果您不在了，您的家人在財務上怎麼辦？", "吳女士，我很多客戶在跟我談之前，跟您想法一樣。我可以分享是什麼改變了他們的想法嗎？"]}
