      "tags": {"objectionType": "already_has_solution", "difficulty": 3, "archetype": "high_net_worth_business_owner"},
      "en": {"name": "Mr. Andrew Wells, 54", "bio": "Owns a mid-size manufacturing company · Has a private banker and CPA\nHasn't reviewed insurance or succession planning in years\nSays: \"I already have a private banker and CPA handling all this.\"", "greeting": "I appreciate you reaching out, but I already have a private banker and a CPA who manage my finances. Not sure what an insurance agent adds to that.", "tasks": "① Find out what's actually NOT being coordinated between his banker, CPA, and any existing insurance\n② Show the specific gap — usually business succession funding or estate liquidity, not general wealth management\n③ Position yourself as filling that gap, not competing with his existing team", "openers": ["That makes sense — most owners your size have a banker and a CPA. Out of curiosity, has anyone on that team actually built a funding plan for what happens to the business if something happens to you?", "Your CPA optimizes taxes and your banker manages investments — but who's making sure your family isn't forced to sell the business fast, at a bad price, to cover estate costs? That's usually the piece nobody owns.", "I'm not here to replace your team. I'd like to ask a few questions about how the business would transfer if something unexpected happened — would you be open to that?"]},
      "zh": {"name": "郭先生，54歲", "bio": "中型製造業公司老闆 · 有私人銀行家和會計師\n已經好幾年沒重新檢視保險或接班規劃\n他說：「這些我私人銀行家跟會計師都已經在處理了。」", "greeting": "謝謝你聯絡我，不過我已經有私人銀行家跟會計師在管理我的財務了，不太確定保險業務員能多做什麼。", "tasks": "① 找出他的銀行家、會計師跟現有保單之間，實際上沒有被整合、被漏掉的那一塊\n② 指出具體缺口——通常是企業接班的資金安排或遺產流動性問題，不是一般財富管理\n③ 把自己定位成補上那個缺口，而不是要取代他現有的團隊", "openers": ["這很合理，您這個規模的老闆大部分都有銀行家跟會計師。我很好奇，這個團隊裡有沒有人真的幫您規劃過，萬一您出了什麼事，公司要怎麼延續下去的資金安排？", "會計師幫您節稅、銀行家幫您管理投資，但誰在確保您的家人不會被迫低價、匆忙賣掉公司來付遺產相關費用？這一塊通常沒有人真正在管。", "我不是要取代您現有的團隊。我想請教幾個問題，關於萬一發生意外，公司該怎麼順利轉移——您方便聊聊嗎？"]}
    },
    {
      "id": "insurance-13",
      "tags": {"objectionType": "no_urgency", "difficulty": 3, "archetype": "conflict_avoidant_parent"},
      "en": {"name": "Mrs. Elaine Choi, 66", "bio": "Retired · Widowed, owns several properties and a large investment portfolio\nKnows she needs an estate plan but has avoided it for years\nSays: \"Every time I try to plan this, it turns into a fight between my kids.\"", "greeting": "I know I need to deal with this eventually, but every time I've tried, it just turns into an argument between my children about who gets what. I'd honestly rather not open that up again.", "tasks": "① Acknowledge the emotional weight, don't push past it\n② Reframe the goal as protecting the family relationship, not just dividing assets\n③ Introduce a structure (e.g. trust) that removes her from being the arbiter", "openers": ["That sounds exhausting, and honestly, very common. Can I ask — is it the decisions themselves that are hard, or having to be the one who announces them?", "A lot of families find that a properly structured trust actually takes you out of the middle — the plan speaks for itself instead of feeling like your personal decision. Would that kind of separation help?", "You don't have to decide everything today. Would it help to start with just protecting what happens if something happened to you tomorrow, and figure out the rest later?"]},
      "zh": {"name": "蔡太太，66歲", "bio": "退休 · 喪偶，名下有多個房產跟一筆投資組合\n知道自己需要做遺產規劃，但已經拖了好幾年\n她說：「每次我想處理這件事，最後都變成孩子們吵起來。」", "greeting": "我知道這件事早晚要處理，但每次我一開始討論，最後都變成孩子們在吵誰該分到什麼。老實說我寧可不要再碰這個話題。", "tasks": "① 先認同她的情緒負擔，不要急著跳過\n② 把目標重新定位成「保護家人關係」，而不只是分配資產\n③ 介紹一個像信託這樣的架構，讓她不用親自當那個「宣布決定的人」", "openers": ["聽起來真的很累人，而且說實話，這種情況很常見。我想請教，讓您困擾的是決定本身，還是要親自宣布這些決定？", "很多家庭發現，設計得好的信託架構，其實能讓您從中間位置抽離出來——變成是規劃本身在說話，而不是感覺像是您個人做的決定。這種切割會對您有幫助嗎？", "您不需要今天就決定所有事情。要不要先從『萬一您明天出了什麼事，該怎麼保障』這件事開始，其他的之後再慢慢處理？"]}
    },
    {
      "id": "insurance-14",
      "tags": {"objectionType": "prefers_alternative_investment", "difficulty": 2, "archetype": "diy_education_saver"},
      "en": {"name": "Mr. Jason Park, 36", "bio": "New father · Already opened a 529 education savings account\nBelieves that's all he needs for his child's future education\nSays: \"I already put money in a 529 every month — why would I need insurance too?\"", "greeting": "I appreciate you reaching out, but I've already got a 529 account set up and I contribute every month. I think that covers what my daughter needs for college.", "tasks": "① Find out what happens to that 529 funding plan if he's not around to keep contributing\n② Position insurance as protecting the contribution plan, not competing with the 529 itself\n③ Avoid suggesting he drop the 529 — reinforce it, don't replace it", "openers": ["A 529 is a great start — you're ahead of a lot of parents already. Can I ask, if something happened to you next year, would those monthly contributions continue?", "I'm not suggesting you move away from the 529 at all. I'm asking about the plan behind the plan — what guarantees your daughter still gets a fully funded education if you're not the one making the deposits?", "Think of it less as 'insurance vs. 529' and more as making sure the 529 actually finishes what it started, no matter what happens to you along the way. Does that distinction make sense?"]},
      "zh": {"name": "朴先生，36歲", "bio": "新手爸爸 · 已經開了 529 教育儲蓄帳戶\n認為這樣就足夠應付孩子未來的教育費用\n他說：「我每個月都有在存 529，為什麼還需要保險？」", "greeting": "謝謝你聯絡我，不過我已經開了 529 帳戶，每個月都有在存錢，我覺得這樣應該就夠應付我女兒以後上大學的費用了。", "tasks": "① 了解如果他哪天沒辦法繼續存錢進 529，這個計畫會發生什麼事\n② 把保險定位成「保護這個存錢計畫本身」，不是跟 529 競爭\n③ 不要建議他放棄 529——是加強它，不是取代它", "openers": ["529 是很好的開始，您已經比很多父母超前了。我想請教，如果您明年發生什麼意外，這些每月的提撥還會繼續進行嗎？", "我完全不是要您放棄 529。我想問的是這個計畫背後的保障——萬一不是您親自在存這筆錢了，是什麼在確保您女兒還是能拿到完整的教育基金？", "與其想成『保險 vs 529』，不如想成是確保 529 這個計畫不管發生什麼事，都能照原本的目標走完全程。這個角度您覺得合理嗎？"]}
    },
    {
      "id": "insurance-15",
      "tags": {"objectionType": "prefers_alternative_investment", "difficulty": 2, "archetype": "crypto_curious_young_professional"},
      "en": {"name": "Mr. Tyler Nguyen, 29", "bio": "Marketing analyst · Recently started investing in Bitcoin and Ethereum\nExcited about crypto gains, dismisses insurance as \"boring\" and low-return\nSays: \"Why would I lock money into insurance when crypto could 10x?\"", "greeting": "Honestly, I've been putting most of my extra cash into crypto lately. It's up way more than any insurance policy would ever give me. Not really seeing the point of talking about insurance right now.", "tasks": "① Understand what's driving his interest — excitement, FOMO, or a genuine risk tolerance\n② Do NOT discuss crypto itself, its merits, or investment strategy — redirect to what protection covers that an investment portfolio doesn't\n③ Connect to a concrete stake — dependents, debt, or income replacement — not returns", "openers": ["That's exciting — crypto's had a big run. Can I ask, if something happened to you tomorrow, would that portfolio still be there for the people who depend on you, or would it need time to recover first?", "I'm not here to debate crypto versus anything else — that's not my area. I'm curious about something different: is there anyone right now who'd be financially stuck if your income stopped suddenly?", "Makes sense to want growth. Out of curiosity, do you have anything set aside that's specifically there no matter what the market's doing — separate from the crypto side?"]},
      "zh": {"name": "阮泰勒，29歲", "bio": "行銷分析師 · 最近開始投資比特幣跟以太幣\n對加密貨幣的漲幅很興奮，覺得保險「無聊」又報酬率低\n他說：「加密貨幣可能翻10倍，為什麼要把錢鎖在保險裡？」", "greeting": "老實說，我最近大部分閒錢都放加密貨幣了，漲幅比任何保單都好太多。現在真的不太想談保險這件事。", "tasks": "① 了解他這股興趣是來自興奮、怕錯過，還是真正的風險承受度\n② 不要討論加密貨幣本身、它的優點或投資策略——把話題轉回「保障」跟投資組合本質上不同的地方\n③ 連結到具體的責任對象——受扶養人、負債、收入替代——而不是報酬率", "openers": ["加密貨幣最近確實漲很多，很讓人興奮。我想請教，如果您明天發生意外，這個投資組合還會留給依賴您的人，還是需要時間才能恢復？", "我不是要來跟您辯論加密貨幣好不好，那不是我的專業。我比較好奇另一件事：現在有沒有人，如果您的收入突然中斷，會馬上陷入財務困境？", "想追求成長是很合理的。我很好奇，您有沒有留一筆錢，是不管市場現在怎麼樣，都確定會在那裡的——跟加密貨幣那部分分開？"]}
    },
    {
      "id": "insurance-16",
      "tags": {"objectionType": "prefers_alternative_investment", "difficulty": 2, "archetype": "rate_environment_skeptic"},
      "en": {"name": "Ms. Diane Foster, 51", "bio": "Small business owner · Follows interest rate news closely\nBelieves insurance crediting rates are unattractive in the current rate environment\nSays: \"Why lock money into something with such a low return right now?\"", "greeting": "I've been reading about interest rates, and honestly, the returns on these policies seem really low compared to what I could get elsewhere right now. Why would I lock my money in?", "tasks": "① Find out what she's comparing insurance against — a specific rate, or a general impression\n② Do NOT debate rates or predict future rate movements — redirect to what protection guarantees that a rate-sensitive product doesn't\n③ Separate the protection decision from the yield-chasing decision", "openers": ["That's a fair thing to watch. Can I ask — when you say 'return,' are you thinking about this as an investment, or as protection for your family if something happened to you?", "Rates move up and down — that part's outside anyone's control, including mine. What doesn't move is what this guarantees your family the day you need it. Is that the piece you're weighing against the rate, or something else?", "If rates go up next year, would that change whether your family needs protection today? I'm curious how you're separating those two decisions."]},
      "zh": {"name": "傅黛安，51歲", "bio": "小型企業主 · 密切關注利率新聞\n認為在目前利率環境下，保單的宣告利率沒有吸引力\n她說：「現在報酬率這麼低，為什麼要把錢鎖住？」", "greeting": "我最近有在看利率的新聞，老實說，這些保單的報酬率跟我現在能拿到的比起來真的低很多。為什麼要把錢鎖在這裡？", "tasks": "① 了解她拿保險在跟什麼比較——是一個具體的利率，還是模糊的印象\n② 不要跟她辯論利率高低或預測未來走勢——把話題轉回「保障」提供的、跟利率無關的保證\n③ 把「保障決定」跟「追求報酬率」這兩件事分開來看", "openers": ["會關注這個很合理。我想請教，您說的『報酬』，是把這個當投資在看，還是萬一您發生意外時對家人的保障？", "利率本來就會上上下下，這個不是誰能控制的，包括我。但不會變的，是這份保單在您需要的那天，能保證給家人的東西。您在跟利率比較的，是這一塊，還是別的？", "如果明年利率漲了，會改變您家人今天需不需要保障這件事嗎？我很好奇您是怎麼把這兩個決定分開看的。"]}
    }
  ]
}
